`PROVINCE_DICT` is a class attribute of `global_lookup`. It is not automatically added to the namespace of the methods. Since you intend to call these methods directly from the class, and since you need access to the class attributes, you should declare these methods as class methods. For example:

    @classmethod
    def get_province_short(cls, province_long):
        for prov_shrt, prov_long in cls.PROVINCE_DICT.items():
            if province_long == prov_long:
                return prov_shrt
            else:
                raise DatahubError(F&quot;get_province_short - Province data for {province_long} could not be located&quot;) 

Note the `@classmethod` decorator which will cause a reference to the class to be added to the method signature. We use that reference (`cls`) to access `PROVINCE_DICT`.

